{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Q2JK6FpNCv7jbPsKTkZefQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pod is running but the readiness probe is failing with 503. This is expected for CockroachDB - all nodes need to start before the cluster is initialized. The readiness probe checks `/health?ready=1` which returns 503 until the cluster is initialized via `cockroach init`.\n\nThe issue is that all 3 pods are trying to form a cluster, but the cluster hasn't been initialized yet. CockroachDB in insecure mode requires running `cockroach init` once all nodes are up.\n\nLet me check if all 3 pods are running first, then run `cockroach init` on one of them.\nActually, I realize we're on a single-node cluster, so the StatefulSet starts pods sequentially - pod-0 first, then pod-1 once pod-0 is Ready. Since pod-0 isn't Ready yet due to the failing readiness probe, the other pods won't start. The pods are stuck waiting in the `--join` state for cluster initialization, but they need the `cockroach init` command to actually form the cluster. The typical insecure setup requires starting all nodes first (they'll wait in an initialization state), then running `cockroach init` on one of them to bootstrap the cluster.\n\nThe issue is that the readiness probe `/health?ready=1` fails until init is complete, but init can't happen until all pods are running. The fix is to change the StatefulSet to use `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all pods start simultaneously without waiting for the previous one to be ready. Then I can run `cockroach init` to bootstrap the cluster. I'll need to delete and recreate the StatefulSet with this policy change.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":764,"cache_read_input_tokens":32151,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":764},"output_tokens":11,"servi