{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FJJHVetRenmyHAvUNkArLK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The headless service has no endpoints! This is because the pods are not Ready (readiness probe is failing). Headless service only registers DNS for pods that are Ready. Since none of the pods are Ready (they're all showing 0/1), the DNS records aren't being created.\n\nThis is a chicken-and-egg problem:\n1. Pods need to start and join cluster before they can pass readiness probe\n2. But the `--join` flag uses pod DNS names which require the headless service DNS\n3. But headless service DNS only works for Ready pods\n4. Pods can't be Ready until they join the cluster via init\n5. Init can't run until pods are running and discoverable\n\nActually, I realize headless services can register DNS for unready pods if I set `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`. By default they only create records for Ready pods, but with that flag enabled, the pod DNS names will resolve even before the readiness probe passes. That's what I need to fix this.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":672,"cache_read_input_tokens":37505,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":672},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f48d1c4-d8fb-419d-8e69-d14b6460ef4b","uuid":"44014ff1-4766-4bb4-8e09-8349d2a63244","request_id":"req_011CbzHX8TNnBNUde7zQqqQG"}
