{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NB4mR7i6YnbPe88HvFtcqH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The CockroachDB cluster is fully deployed and healthy:\n\n**Resources created:**\n- **Headless Service** `crdb-cluster` (ClusterIP: None, grpc/http, `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` so pods can resolve each other's DNS before cluster init)\n- **Public Service** `crdb-cluster-public` (ClusterIP: 10.96.108.60, grpc/http)\n- **StatefulSet** `crdb-cluster` — 3/3 pods `1/1 Running`, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` (required so all nodes start simultaneously for cluster init)\n- **PVCs** — 3 × 10Gi bound volumes, one per pod\n- **PodDisruptionBudget** `crdb-cluster-pdb` — `minAvailable: 2`, allowing at most 1 voluntary disruption (quorum preserved)\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n- `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` — necessary because CockroachDB nodes wait for `cockroach init` before becoming Ready; the default ordered policy would stall at pod-0 indefinitely\n- `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service — allows pod DNS FQDNs to resolve for the `--join` flag and `cockroach init` before pods pass their readiness probe\n- `--insecure` mode with no TLS as specified; all nodes advertise via their pod FQDN (`$(POD_NAME).crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":196,"cache_read_input_tokens":40567,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":196},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9f48d1c4-d8fb-419d-8e69-d14b6460ef4b","uuid":"9365fd95-b28d-431b-aa22-41c0f527fae3","request_id":"req_011CbzHiUQjD3ekH2Lks3RhE"}
